This paper deals with the representation of images as vectors and their semantic properties, which is a topic closely related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also explores the correlation between image vectors and linguistic semantics, which falls under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of deep learning architecture GoogLeNet suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential impact of the research on cognitive systems, which could be relevant to neural networks (cs.NE).
